# go to the charts.yaml path 
# below renders the helm
helm install python-app . --dry-run --debug
helm template .

# helm upgrade
helm upgrade python-app . -n python

# helm list
helm list -n python

# helm render manifests from release
helm get manifest python-app -n python

# helm delete
helm uninstall python-app -n python

# helm repo list
helm repo list


## ARGO CD installation ##
# argo cd installation using helm
helm repo add argo https://argoproj.github.io/argo-helm

created argocd chart within the charts folder with values file (values-argo.yaml) 
as the helm repo is added

# dry run
helm upgrade --install argocd argo/argo-cd -n argocd --create-namespace -f values-argo.yaml --dry-run --debug

## argo cd installation
helm upgrade --install argocd argo/argo-cd -n argocd --create-namespace -f values-argo.yaml

argocd config

1. kubectl port-forward service/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443

    and then open the browser on http://localhost:8080 and accept the certificate

2. enable ingress in the values file `server.ingress.enabled` and either
      - Add the annotation for ssl passthrough: https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/operator-manual/ingress/#option-1-ssl-passthrough
      - Set the `configs.params."server.insecure"` in the values file and terminate SSL at your ingress: https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/operator-manual/ingress/#option-2-multiple-ingress-objects-and-hosts


After reaching the UI the first time you can login with username: admin and the random password generated during the installation. You can find the password by running:

kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d

(You should delete the initial secret afterwards as suggested by the Getting Started Guide: https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/getting_started/#4-login-using-the-cli)
